{"type":"message","id":"ba8a37fd","parentId":"1739fa5e","timestamp":"2026-05-15T12:40:01.909Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have TikTok Vietnam data. Let me analyze the candidate products that meet the criteria:\n- 上架＜3个月新品\n- 近4周销量持续上涨，无下滑\n- 中小达人（1w–5w粉）带货为主，无头部卖家垄断\n- 商品评分≥4.5\n- 价格带适配越南站\n\nLooking at the data, I need to find products with positive weekly growth (周销量环比). Let me filter:\n\nFrom similar_product search for \"Kẹp tóc nơ\":\n1. \n\nI'm checking the velvet cat clip with weekly growth of 6846 units and 18578 monthly sales - this one shows strong momentum. Looking at the other candidates, the duck bill clip with 804 weekly and 4901 monthly also has good engagement, and the metal duck bill combo appears to be another solid option to evaluate. Looking at the weekly growth rates for the remaining candidates, most are showing declines which doesn't match the requirement for sustained upward momentum. The claw clip with the whale design at 18,578 monthly sales is showing the strongest growth at +40.26%, making it the clear winner so far. I'm cross-referencing these candidates against the category report data to verify which ones show positive weekly momentum and meet the 3-month listing requirement. The duck bill claw clip with 40.26% weekly growth is clearly the strongest performer, followed by the other top-sellers in the Vietnamese market. Now I'm checking the new products launched within three months that are showing promising sales traction. Looking at the weekly growth rates for these top performers, most are showing declines which doesn't match the requirement for positive momentum. The banana clip stands out with nearly 40% growth, while the other candidates show either modest gains or steep drops week-over-week.\n\nHowever, I need to reconsider the timeline constraint—items with over 10,000 monthly sales and established review counts are likely older than three months, so the new entrants with smaller but growing sales volumes are probably better candidates for this requirement.\n\nLooking at the newer products from the category report data, those launched within three months have much lower sales volumes (23693 total across 26 items), which actually aligns better with a fresh product requirement. Let me pull the 1688 pricing for these specific items to complete the analysis.\n\nFor the cost calculation, I realize I don't have the user's actual formula yet, but based on Vietnamese TikTok Shop operations, I can work with standard parameters: the product cost from 1688, shipping to a forwarder warehouse in China, then to Vietnam with customs duties, platform fees around 3-5% plus payment processing, and finally the selling price on TikTok Vietnam.\n\nNow I'm selecting high-potential products from the data—focusing on items with positive growth trends, strong ratings above 4.5, and price points that allow for healthy margins. The princess crown bow clip with 18,578 monthly sales and 4.5 stars looks particularly strong, and I'm also considering the velvet cat hair clip with 8,765 monthly sales and an excellent 4.8 rating as a solid backup option.\n","thinkingSignature":"eb9ec4fc2fdb2cfa858057686364f0a0240143c31f0c36ca06cb6cc9fd720723"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vfrkusf4hist_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter call sorftime-test.tiktok_similar_product searchName=\"Kẹp tóc càng cua\" page=1 site=VN --output json 2>&1","yieldMs":20000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vfrkusf4hist_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter call sorftime-test.tiktok_similar_product searchName=\"băng đô tóc\" page=1 site=VN --output json 2>&1","yieldMs":20000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5633,"output":774,"cacheRead":49920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56327,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778848766120,"responseId"