{"type":"message","id":"224f8009","parentId":"2d0173de","timestamp":"2026-05-15T12:41:27.598Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user confirmed that the key `rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09` is the correct one. They also asked if there's anything that needs adjusting. Let me continue with the product selection process.\n\nI had gathered:\n1. Amazon hair clips/hoops/pins product features - good data\n2. TikTok Vietnam category report for hair clips (nodeId 908552) - good data with Top50 products\n3. TikTok similar products for various searches\n\nNow I need to:\n- Look for products that are:\n  - New (< 3 months on market)\n  - Growing sales trend\n  - Mid-tier influencers (1w-5w followers) driving sales\n  - Rating ≥ 4.5\n  - Price range suitable for Vietnam\n  - Not ultra-low price war products\n\nFrom the category report data I already have, let me identify candidates. The data shows:\n- Top10 products monthly sales concentration is 22.02% (not too monopolized)\n- Top10 seller concentration is 44.89% (moderate)\n\n\n- 26 new products within 3 months with 23,693 monthly sales\n\nNow I'm filtering through the top performers for items with positive or stable weekly sales growth, ratings of 4.5 or higher, and price points between 15,000-50,000 VND that would appeal to Vietnam. The banana clip by ALIA looks promising with 10,768 monthly sales and a 4.7 rating, though the weekly decline of 22% is concerning. I'm also checking the Korean-style hair clip from the same vendor. Looking at the hair accessories data, the magic velcro headband stands out with nearly 32,000 reviews and a positive weekly trend, suggesting strong market demand for this hair styling accessory in the Vietnamese market.\n\nFor the cost analysis, I'm calculating the landed cost from 1688 suppliers by factoring in the product price, shipping from China to Vietnam, and platform fees to determine viable pricing margins.\n\nHowever, I notice the 1688 MCP tool isn't available on the sorftime-test server, so I need to explore alternative approaches or determine if there's another way to access supplier pricing data for these items.\n","thinkingSignature":"e6dd006b0ffbd8ba2baf6767d6640c09afde4d5867c7bbead0a70cd6f86e2167"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oi85zbgasucy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter list sorftime-test 2>&1 | grep -i \"ali\\|1688\\|similar\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":843,"output":502,"cacheRead":57984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59329,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778848865329,"responseId":"06564761b97aee7956ad6de94b739246"}}
