{"type":"message","id":"c494fc7c","parentId":"20817b43","timestamp":"2026-05-15T12:42:12.953Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, there's `ali1688_similar_product` in the sorftime-test server. Now let me check the config to make sure it's using the working key `rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09` for sorftime-test. Yes it is. Now let me proceed with the 1688 sourcing for top candidates.\n\nFrom the TikTok data, the most promising candidates based on:\n1. Rising weekly sales (positive growth)\n2. High rating ≥4.5\n3. Vietnamese-market suitable (Korean style, cute, etc.)\n4. Within 3 months (new products)\n\n\n5. Medium price range suitable for Vietnam\n\nLooking at the top performers, I'm seeing several standouts: a princess bow clip with 6846 weekly and 18578 monthly sales, a cute cat velvet clip at 957 weekly, a large claw clip in Korean style at 944 weekly, a sparkly bow clip at 1580 weekly, and a trendy 2025 ribbon clip at 1130 weekly.\n\nNow I'm pulling pricing data from 1688 to verify supply costs. The hair clip categories I'm focusing on are snap clips, hair ties, hair bands, bobby pins, and claw clips across Vietnamese translations like kẹp tóc, dây buộc tóc, and băng đô.\n\nI'm starting to source the top candidates - beginning with a big bow hair clip retailing at 19,999 VND from Five Stars Jewelry Store, a Korean-style large acrylic hair clip at 18,000 VND from ALIA, and a cute cat-shaped velvet clip at 25,379 VND from LSN Toy.\n\nNow I'm continuing with additional hair clip options - a bouncy ribbon clip priced at 8,998 VND from Kim Nguyên Bến Tre with strong sales and rating, a large beaded balloon clip from Vua Kẹp Tóc at 48,800 VND, and a puff-creating hair clip at 22,899 VND also from Vua Kẹp Tóc.\n\nI'm realizing I need to recalibrate my approach - the user mentioned 30092 uses remaining on the rhblyi key, but that's tied to the sorftime-test MCP server. The sorftime-mcp server uses a different key entirely, so I should verify which one the user is actually referencing when they mention remaining uses.\n\nFor the sourcing step, I need to figure out the right approach with the available tools. I have the similar product search function that takes a product name and optional marketplace parameters, but I'm trying to determine whether I should search for the actual Vietnamese product names as they appear on TikTok Shop or use the Chinese 1688 platform equivalents instead.\n\nMy strategy is to search for each product on 1688 using the Vietnamese names and see what comes back. I'm planning to look up eight different products: the big bow knot clips, the cat-shaped velvet clips, the Korean-style large acrylic clips, the puff-creating clips, the large beaded balloon clips, the cute bobby pins, the băng đô hairband, and the 60-piece Korean-style pins.\n\nLooking at the actual data I've collected, the best performers are a 6-piece elastic hair tie set with 30,285 monthly sales at 16,999 VND, a 136-piece colorful hair tie set with 23,470 monthly sales at 44,999 VND, a banana clip for ponytails with 10,768 monthly sales at 17,000 VND, and a Korean-style multi-color ball point clip with 9,783 monthly sales at 16,000 VND. The hairband category isn't performing as well, so I should focus on the clips and ties instead.\n\nI'm realizing I need to stick strictly to the hair accessories scope—发饰 means hair accessories, specifically headbands, clips, and pins—so I should exclude the turbans and focus on these four TikTok bestsellers to find their 1688 sourcing prices. I'm realizing I need to focus on the core products and work backwards from what actually sells. Let me search for the top performers on 1688 using their actual product names rather than trying to map every variation, then I can calculate actual costs and margins.\n","thinkingSignature":"f9e832ac0022b732445244256794df657894e77df49b5d5c0f0cd072883fc920"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oytgbgfizb8n_1","name":"exec","argum