{"type":"message","id":"c8734a88","parentId":"14b5912e","timestamp":"2026-05-15T12:49:38.126Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the product selection strategy \"选品策略2.0 26.5.14\" - they want to know how this strategy looks (they might be referring to a Feishu document they have). They haven't provided the Feishu link yet, but they're asking about the strategy itself.\n\nWait - looking at the context, they previously sent me a detailed product selection strategy prompt. Now they're asking \"这个策略怎么样\" - how is this strategy? They might be asking me to evaluate the strategy they sent earlier (the one starting with \"你是专属越南TikTok Shop时尚配件\\-发饰类目选品Agent\").\n\nLet me think about what they want. They previously provided a detailed strategy with:\n\n\n- Cost calculation formula (which they said I must use exactly)\n- MCP call order (Amazon → TikTok → 1688)\n- Scoring weights\n- Elimination rules\n- Feishu multi-dimensional table entry rules\n\nAnd they asked me to execute the full workflow. I started executing but didn't complete it due to not having the Feishu link.\n\nNow they're asking \"这个策略怎么样\" - how is this strategy? They might want feedback on the strategy itself. Let me give them my evaluation of the strategy: what works well, what could be improved, and any gaps I notice.\n\nLet me also note - I didn't get the Feishu table link they provided. The message was just about the strategy itself.\n\nLooking at the strategy they've outlined, it's actually quite solid - the structured approach with MCP integration, the emphasis on Vietnamese market fit, the 35% profit margin threshold as a hard cutoff, and the cross-platform validation through Amazon, TikTok, and 1688 all make sense. The 100-point scoring system with specific weights gives good structure, and the elimination red lines are clear. But there are some gaps worth mentioning: the cost calculation formula they mentioned isn't actually in the prompt, the strategy assumes the Feishu table is already set up but doesn't cover the schema or column structure, and I need to understand what cost components they're using - product cost, shipping, platform fees, marketing spend, etc.\n","thinkingSignature":"ec203262df9f907d59513fcee0719b4db56499fcd2c5be43685ac5f80ac12768"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你发的那套策略框架整体很扎实，但有几个可以优化的点：\n\n---\n\n## ✅ 策略优点\n\n1. **MCP调用顺序固定** — 先亚马逊锁定爆款基因，再TikTok越南站验证销量趋势，最后1688核成本，逻辑链完整\n2. **35%净利润硬门槛** — 避免进入低价内卷泥潭\n3. **中小达人占比作为竞争友好度指标** — 这个维度很好，比单纯看销量更准确\n4. **3个月内新品 + 持续上涨** — 排除了衰退品，抓趋势品的能力强\n5. **飞书入库控制Top3-10** — 避免表格堆砌海量数据，保持可操作性\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ 几个可以加强的点\n\n### 1. 成本公式没给出来\n你反复强调\"**严格使用我提供的固定成本&利润计算公式**\"，但策略里没有附上公式本身。我没法知道你的参数：\n- 平台扣点是多少？（TikTok越南站抽佣比例）\n- 广告预留比例？\n- 物流费按什么算？\n- 是否包含货代/仓储/退款预留？\n\n**建议补充：**\n```\n到手利润 = 售价 - 拿货价 - 国际物流 - 平台佣金 - 广告预留 - 退款预留\n净利润率 = 到手利润 / 售价\n```\n\n### 2. 亚马逊爆款特征没有区分\"越南适配\"权重\n亚马逊热销≠越南热销。比如美国爆款可能偏金色/深色，但越南女生更偏好粉色/奶油色/白色。策略里应该加一个\"**越南审美适配度**\"子维度，而不是只看销量。\n\n### 3. \"竞争友好度\"指标缺少量化标准\n\"中小达人（1w–5w粉）带货为主，无头部卖家垄断\" — 这个判断是定性的。我建议具体化：\n- Top10卖家市场份额占比 < 30% → 竞争友好\n- Top50中1w-5w粉达人数 > 10个 → 达人生态健康\n\n### 4. 1688筛选标准缺少最低起订量红线\n如果1688起订量500件以上，对于初测款来说资金压力太大。建议加一条：起订量≤100件的供应商优先。\n\n---\n\n## 📋 建议补充的规则\n\n| 遗漏项 | 建议加入 |\n|---|---|\n| 成本公式参数 | 平台佣金%、广告预留%、物流费估算公式 |\n| 越南审美适配 | 韩系/可爱/马卡龙色/小清新 = 优先；欧美夸张/暗黑 = 排除 |\n| 竞争量化标准 | Top10卖家份额、达人分布比例 |\n| 起订量限制 | 起订量>200件的款直接淘汰 |\n| 新品定义 | 上架<3个月 or 评论<100条 |\n\n---\n\n**你要不要把成本公式发给我？** 我之前跑的利润估算用的是通用比例，不是你实际的成本结构，可能有偏差。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1375,"output":1053,"cacheRead":78144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778849332479,"responseId":"065649348033d031d1adce7e669ffec5"}}
