{"type":"message","id":"c9b32042","parentId":"6dec9857","timestamp":"2026-05-15T13:19:16.841Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the cost formula parameters. Let me understand the structure:\n\n**Fee Items:**\n- 平台佣金费率: 13%\n- 交易手续费率: 3.5%\n- 增值税率: 12%\n- 提现手续费率: 1%\n- SFP 服务费率: 0%\n- 达人佣金费率: 10%\n\nSo the cost structure for Vietnam TikTok Shop seems to be:\n- Platform commission: 13%\n- Transaction fee: 3.5%\n- VAT: 12%\n- Withdrawal fee: 1%\n- SFP service fee: 0%\n- Influencer/KOL commission: 10%\n\nTotal deduction before product cost = 13% + 3.5% + 12% + 1% + 0% + 10% = 39.5%\n\nWait, but some of these might be calculated differently. Let me think about the typical formula:\n\nSelling Price → minus Product Cost → minus Platform Commission → minus Transaction Fee → minus VAT → minus Influencer Commission → minus Logistics → minus Ad Reserve → = Net Profit\n\n\nI'm not entirely sure of the exact sequence these fees apply in, so I should ask for the complete formula. In the meantime, I can structure it as: net revenue equals selling price minus platform fees (which total around 29.5% when combining the 13% commission, 3.5% transaction fee, and 12% VAT), minus influencer commissions at 10%, minus withdrawal fees at 1%, minus logistics costs and advertising reserves.\n\nOnce I have the full calculation from the user, I'll apply the formula to each product I've identified. I've gathered key items like the velvet flower clip at 35,000 VND, the floral headband at 34,780 VND, and the bangs adhesive at 14,999 VND, and I need to cross-reference these with their corresponding 1688 supplier prices to compute the actual profit margins. I'm working through the profit margin calculation with the exchange rate, but I'm missing some key formulas from the image the user shared. I should ask for the full calculation formula including all the deductions like platform fees, influencer commissions, and logistics costs so I can give them accurate numbers.\n\nFor now, I'll estimate the net margin by combining the platform commission, transaction fee, VAT, withdrawal fee, and KOL rate (totaling around 29.5-39.5%), then subtract from the selling price and divide by selling price to get the margin percentage. But I need to verify the correct calculation order before I can confidently compute their specific products.\n\nLooking at their provided rates—13% platform commission, 3.5% transaction fee, 12% VAT, 1% withdrawal fee, and 10% influencer commission—I should apply these systematically to each of the 6 candidate products they selected, starting with the ones that showed positive growth like the hair powder puff clip at 22,500 VND and the floral hair band at 34,780 VND. I'm continuing through the remaining product calculations, working through a large silk bow clip at 39,000 VND, an 8,998 VND crab claw bow clip, a 9,000 VND option, and starting to look at another product in the 16,000 VND range.\n\nI notice I'm missing some critical data—I don't have the 1688 cost prices for most items, I don't have the logistics cost for Vietnam, and I don't have the ad reserve percentage. Without these key inputs, my calculations will be incomplete. I should ask the user to provide the missing cost formula image directly so I can fill in these gaps, or ask them to specify what additional costs need to be factored in.\n\nSince they've already provided the rate structure (13%, 3.5%, 12%, 1%, 0%, 10%), I could try to build the formula myself if I knew the logical sequence, but I'm uncertain about the exact order of calculations and which fees are applied before others. I should ask for the image or a clear statement of the formula so I can complete this properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"d937e57ae67dcd3656396e57486ecac31257d578cf40dc7d5978487d8beeec29"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n收到了费率结构，但我还需要**完整的计算公式**才能准确核算。截图里的公式部分还没发过来，麻烦把公式文字也发我。\n\n另外几个缺失的关键参数：\n1. **1688拿货价** — 我目前查到的价格需要你确认（哪些款要入库？）\n2. **国际物流费**（越南站）— 每件多少 VND