{"type":"message","id":"5fa27b37","parentId":"287f393f","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:00:34.635Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"商品名称 works! So the issue is with numeric fields that have formatters. Let me try with the numeric field without the formatter property - maybe I need to use field_id for those. Let me also try using the field name without the formatter and see if it works.\n\nActually wait - earlier with just \"文本\" it worked, then with \"商品名称\" it also worked. The problem is with numeric fields like \"售价本地货币\". The API is saying \"field_name not found\" for \"售价本地货币\". \n\nMaybe the issue is that some field names have special characters or the field type. Let me try using field_id for the numeric fields.\n\nActually - looking at the error: \"fields.售价本地货币\" - this is the field name. It seems like even though the API accepts \"文本\" and \"商品名称\", it doesn't accept \"售价本地货币\". \n\nBut earlier when I first tried, I got errors for ALL fields. Now only the numeric ones fail. Let me try with 月销量 and other fields. The API is rejecting the field name itself, not the value format, so maybe I need to use field_id instead. Since the test with just \"文本\" and \"商品名称\" both worked, the issue seems specific to numeric fields with formatters - I should try accessing them directly by field_id rather than by name. I see the issue now - the `formatter` property I added was from the field metadata response, but it's not actually a valid input parameter when creating records. I should be using just the raw numeric value and let the field's default formatting handle it.\n\nLet me test with \"月销量\" alone to see if that's the problematic field, then check if the `formatter` in the DateTime field is also causing issues when I include \"日期\".\n","thinkingSignature":"c475b27d18df2e5ec1a7708d96d9c2cdbc52d53a495fdef8241de132fda1a602"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_knaqu6owyym2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"APP_ID=\"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\"\nAPP_SECRET=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']['appSecret'])\")\n\nTOKEN=$(curl -s \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\\\"app_id\\\":\\\"$APP_ID\\\",\\\"app_secret\\\":\\\"$APP_SECRET\\\"}\" | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('tenant_access_token',''))\")\n\n# Try 月销量 (number field) alone\ncurl -s -X POST \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bitable/v1/apps/AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd/tables/tblHU2do30jzinJT/records\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8\" \\\n  --data-raw '{\n    \"fields\": {\n      \"文本\": \"2026-05-15 测试-月销\",\n      \"商品名称\": \"Lò xo cột tóc thailann\",\n      \"月销量\": 4888\n    }\n  }' | python3 -m json.tool 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1081,"output":700,"cacheRead":100928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102709,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778853617822,"responseId":"065659f2c59e5c3c9fe589dddb953e81"}}
{"type":"message","id":"57dac043","parentId":"5fa27b37","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:00:36.787Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_knaqu6owyym2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n    \"code\": 0,\n    \"data\": {\n        \"record\": {\n            \"fields\": {\n                \"\\u5546\\u54c1\\u540d\\u79f0\": \"L\\u00f2 xo c\\u1ed9t t\\u00f3c thailann\",\n                \"\\u6587\\u672c\": \"2026-05-15 \\u6d4b\\u8bd5-\\u6708\\u9500\",\n                \"\\u6708\\u9500\\u91cf\": 4888\n            },\n            \"id\": \"recvjHizw3Ge1T\",\n            \"record_id\": \"recvjHizw3Ge1T\"\n        }\n    },\n    \"msg\": \"success\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2144,"aggregated":"{\n    \"code\": 0,\n    \"data\": {\n        \"record\": {\n            \"fields\": {\n                \"\\u5546\\u54c1\\u540d\\u79f0\": \"L\\u00f2 xo c\\u1ed9t t\\u00f3c thailann\",\n                \"\\u6587\\u672c\": \"2026-05-15 \\u6d4b\\u8bd5-\\u6708\\u9500\",\n                \"\\u6708\\u9500\\u91cf\": 4888\n            },\n            \"id\": \"recvjHizw3Ge1T\",\n            \"record_id\": \"recvjHizw3Ge1T\"\n        }\n    },\n    \"msg\": \"success\"\n}","cwd":"/home/halei/workspace-tts"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778853636787}}
{"type":"message","id":"a2758e92","parentId":"57dac043","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:01:35.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It works! So the issue was:\n1. \"文本\" works\n2. \"商品名称\" works\n3. \"月销量\" works\n4. But \"售价本地货币\" doesn't work - maybe the field name encoding is different (the API seems to be using the raw string as key, so maybe it's a different encoding issue)\n\nLet me try with the URL-encoded field name or check if the issue is with Chinese field names that have special characters or something. \n\nActually wait - \"售价本地货币\" failed, but \"月销量\" worked. Let me check the difference:\n- 售价本地货币 - type: 2 (Number), ui_type: Number, formatter: \"0.0\"\n\n\n- 月销量 - type: 2 (Number), ui_type: Number, formatter: \"0.0\"\n\nBoth are number fields with the same type and formatter, but only 月销量 works. The issue might be with how the Chinese characters are encoded when sent as JSON. Let me try using the field_id directly instead of field_name to see if that resolves the encoding problem.\n\nThe error message shows the backend is receiving \"fields.售价本地货币\" as bytes, so the question is whether my Python string encoding matches what the server expects - UTF-8 for JSON should handle these characters fine, so something else might be going wrong. I'm suspecting the JSON payload encoding might be the culprit here—my `echo` and `curl` commands might not be handling the Chinese characters correctly. Let me try constructing the request differently using Python to ensure proper JSON encoding, or verify whether the issue is specifically with certain field names like \"售价本地货币\" which seems to fail while others like \"月销量\" work fine.\n\nThe error `1254045 FieldNameNotFound` indicates the server can't find the field name, which suggests either a character encoding mismatch between my request and what the server expects, or the field names themselves might be stored differently in the API. Let me map out which fields work and which don't to identify the pattern.\n\nLooking at the successful writes, I can write to \"文本\", \"商品名称\", \"月销量\", and there's one more that works. But \"售价本地货币\" and \"1688价格CNY\" both fail—this suggests the issue isn't just Chinese character encoding since \"商品名称\" works fine. It might be related to the field type or formatter properties, or possibly how certain field names are stored in the system. Let me try a different encoding approach or check the bitable field names more carefully.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the Feishu API documentation might use `field_name` as the key in the fields object, but the actual implementation could be using different key names entirely. Let me just test each field one at a time to identify which ones are actually usable, then build a Python script to handle the batch insert properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"43bbe223dc2f60b4fe90f0df557afda645211374884796332f1da906c6db4fb1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q6iv0zo4wwrk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"APP_ID=\"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\"\nAPP_SECRET=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']['appSecret'])\")\n\nTOKEN=$(curl -s \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\\\"app_id\\\":\\\"$APP_ID\\\",\\\"app_secret\\\":\\\"$APP_SECRET\\\"}\" | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('tenant_access_token',''))\")\n\n# Test each field individually\npython3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport subprocess, json\n\nAPP_ID = \"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\"\nAPP_SECRET = \"sWYftqexbMf6p1fYdJxqGn9U\"\n\ntoken_resp = subprocess.check_output([\n    'curl', '-s', 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal',\n    '-H', 'Content-Type: application/json',\n    '-d', f'{{\"app_id\":\"{APP_ID}\",\"app_secret\":\"{APP_SECRET}\"}}'\n], text=True)\nTOKEN = json.loads(token_resp)['tenant_access_token']\n\nbase_url = \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bitable/v1/apps/AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd/tables/tblHU2do30jzinJT/records\"\n\nfields_to_test = [\n    (\"文本\", \"测试文本字段\"),\n    (\"商品名称\", \"测试商品名字段\"),\n    (\"月销量\", 4888),\n    (\"增长率\", -14.3),\n    (\"售价本地货币\", 59000),\n    (\"1688价格CNY\", 2.5),\n    (\"预计利润\", 16.8),\n    (\"利润率(%)\", 28.5),\n]\n\nfor fname, fvalue in fields_to_test:\n    payload = json.dumps({\"fields\": {\"文本\": \"2026-05-15\", fname: fvalue}}, ensure_ascii=False)\n    result = subprocess.run([\n        'curl', '-s', '-X', 'POST', base_url,\n        '-H', f'Authorization: Bearer {TOKEN}',\n        '-H', 'Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8',\n        '-d', payload\n    ], capture_output=True, text=True)\n    resp = json.loads(result.stdout)\n    if resp.get('code') == 0:\n        print(f\"✅ {fname} = {fvalue} OK\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"❌ {fname} = {fvalue} → {resp.get('code')} {resp.get('msg')}\")\nPYEOF","yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":562,"output":1220,"cacheRead":101952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103734,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778853636902,"responseId":"06565a056d6da11b0df80cac265f6f01"}}
