{"type":"message","id":"7b9c3af4","parentId":"e2b5faa6","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:03:01.575Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So 售价本地货币 works when sent alone? No wait - same error. So \"售价本地货币\" always fails.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe the issue is that when I include other fields, the combined payload has some encoding issue. Let me try a different JSON encoding approach.\n\nOr maybe the issue is related to the Number field having a formatter property (formatter: \"0.0\"). The field has a specific format required. Let me try passing the number differently.\n\nActually, wait - the issue might be that the number field type=2 requires the value to be passed in a specific way. Let me look at the error more carefully: \"invalid param: 'fields.售价本地货币'. Correct format: field_name not found.\"\n\nThis says \"field_name not found\" - which is confusing because earlier it worked for 商品名称 (also a text field). So the issue might be the encoding of the Chinese characters when combined with the number field.\n\n\nLet me test by removing the number field and sending the data as pure ASCII to see if that's the real culprit.\n","thinkingSignature":"3798c6872e63073b8bad400e3dabd9c6d77a2dad60ef35a7005d667266423e43"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_blkel2ikosh3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"APP_ID=\"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\"\nAPP_SECRET=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']['appSecret'])\")\n\nTOKEN=$(curl -s \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\\\"app_id\\\":\\\"$APP_ID\\\",\\\"app_secret\\\":\\\"$APP_SECRET\\\"}\" | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('tenant_access_token',''))\")\n\n# Test with only ASCII-safe text fields to isolate encoding issue\ncurl -s -X POST \"https://open.feishu.cn/ope