{"type":"message","id":"56dccce0","parentId":"cc41bc90","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:04:11.795Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue. Some fields work (文本, 商品名称, 月销量, 增长率, 三级类目, 站点) while others don't (售价本地货币, 1688价格CNY, 预计利润, 利润率, 1688链接). \n\nThe fields that don't work are the ones where the field name contains characters that need URL encoding or special handling. But wait - `增长率` works but `预计利润` doesn't. Both are plain Chinese characters.\n\nActually wait - I think the issue is that `1688价格CNY` and `预计利润` and `利润率` and `1688链接` all have something in common. \n\nLooking at the API response error more carefully, the issue is with the JSON serialization itself. When the server receives the field name as `fields.\\u552e\\u4ef7\\u672c\\u5730\\u8d27\\u5e01`, it's URL-decoding to `售价本地货币` but saying it doesn't exist. This suggests the curl command with `--data-raw` might not be handling the UTF-8 JSON encoding properly, even though `-H \"Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8\"` is set.\n\nTesting with ASCII-only field names worked, so the problem seems to be specific to certain characters. I notice the failed fields all have special characters like the yen symbol, parentheses, or percentage signs, while the working ones like `增长率` and `月销量` don't. But `文本` also has characters and it works, so that's not the full picture.\n\nLooking more closely, the working fields are pure Chinese without symbols, while the failing ones all contain either `(` or `%` or other special characters. I suspect the curl command's `--data-raw` flag might be interfering with JSON encoding. Let me try switching to `-d` instead and use proper string escaping to handle the UTF-8 encoding correctly, or encode the body as a separate variable first to avoid shell interpretation issues.\n","thinkingSignature":"55ec7cc63123d6c6ae61d98ebbdaf9a4c4a0496bb4dc0bb952dd7b80d7d9a9fc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_omsb56ndxp6j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"APP_ID=\"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\"\nAPP_SECRET=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']['appSecret'])\")\n\nTOKEN=$(curl -s \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\\\"app_id\\\":\\\"$APP_ID\\\",\\\"app_secret\\\":\\\"$APP_SECRET\\\"}\" | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('tenant_access_token',''))\")\n\n# Use python to make the request with proper JSON encoding\npython3 << PYEOF\nimport subprocess, json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\nAPP_ID = \"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\"\nAPP_SECRET = \"sWYftqexbMf6p1fYdJxqGn9U\"\n\n# Get token\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal',\n    data=json.dumps({\"app_id\": APP_ID, \"app_secret\": APP_SECRET}).encode(),\n    headers={'Content-Type': 'application/json'}\n)\nwith urllib.request.urlopen(req) as r:\n    TOKEN = json.loads(r.read())['tenant_access_token']\n\nbase_url = \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bitable/v1/apps/AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd/tables/tblHU2do30jzinJT/records\"\n\n# Test fields with special characters\ntest_cases = [\n    (\"售价本地货币\", 69999),\n    (\"1688价格CNY\", 2.5),\n    (\"预计利润\", 16.8),\n    (\"利润率\", 28.5),\n    (\"1688链接\", \"https://detail.1688.com/offer/123456.html\"),\n]\n\nfor fname, fvalue in test_cases:\n    payload = {\"fields\": {\"文本\": \"2026-05-15\", \"商品名称\": f\"Test {fname}\", fname: fvalue}}\n    data = json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False).encode('utf-8')\n    req = urllib.request.Request(\n        base_url, data=data,\n        headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {TOKEN}', 'Content-Type': 'application/json; charset=utf-8'},\n        method='POST'\n    )\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req) as r:\n            resp = json.loads(r.read())\n            if resp.get('code') == 0:\n                print(f\"✅ {fname} = {fvalue}\")\n            else:\n                print(f\"❌ {fname} = {fvalue} → {resp.get('code')} {resp.get('msg')}\")\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        body = e.read().decode()\n        print(f\"❌ {fname} → HTTP {e.code}: {body[:200]}\")\nPYEOF","yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1417,"output":1090,"cacheRead":105408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107915,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778853819264,"responseId":"06565abbca2fb197f1dfddf5530c185a"}}
