{"type":"message","id":"baf168da","parentId":"6d2b4790","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:06:49.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I know exactly which fields work and which don't:\n\n✅ Working:\n- 文本 (primary)\n- 商品名称\n- 月销量\n- 增长率\n- 三级类目\n- 站点\n- 推荐等级\n- 采集状态\n- IP风险\n- 行动建议\n\n❌ Not working:\n- 售价本地货币\n- 1688价格CNY\n- 预计利润\n- 利润率\n- 1688链接\n\nThese fields have names that might be causing encoding issues or are structured differently. Let me try using the raw field names in the JSON.\n\nWait - actually \"售价本地货币\" and \"1688价格CNY\" are Chinese characters that were URL-encoded. \n\nThe issue might be that the field names contain characters that get normalized differently. I should try passing these fields in a single request to see if that resolves the encoding mismatch, and check if there's a specific pattern like \"CNY\" causing the problem. I'm noticing that numeric fields with `formatter: \"0.0\"` are failing - specifically the four fields with this property all returned `FieldNameNotFound` errors. The formula syntax with `%` might be interpreted differently by the API, so I should test removing the formatter constraint to see if that's what's blocking the field access. I'm realizing the issue might be with how I'm constructing the JSON payload—I'm sending field names as Chinese characters directly, but the API might expect the raw field names as they appear in the table rather than URL-encoded versions. Let me try a different approach with explicit formatting for the curl request and test with a simpler numeric value first to isolate whether the problem is with the field name syntax or the value itself.\n","thinkingSignature":"7037db1ef58d070e4d09ed758613d8a214f5147e2d789286fdd936a0f6fab0ee"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5ez2owab7osu_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport subprocess, json, urllib.request, urllib.error, sys\n\n# Get APP_SECRET from openclaw config\nresult = subprocess.run(['cat', '/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json'], capture_output=True, text=True)\nconfig = json.loads(result.stdout)\naccounts = config['channels']['feishu']['accounts']\ntts = accounts.get('tts', {})\nAPP_ID = tts.get('appId', '')\nAPP_SECRET = tts.get('appSecret', '')\n\n# Get token via curl\nresult = subprocess.run([\n    'curl', '-s', 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal',\n    '-H', 'Content-Type: application/json',\n    '-d', json.dumps({\"app_id\": APP_ID, \"app_secret\": APP_SECRET})\n], capture_output=True, text=True)\nresp = json.loads(result.stdout)\nTOKEN = resp['tenant_access_token']\n\nbase_url = \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bitable/v1/apps/AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd/tables/tblHU2do30jzinJT/records\"\n\ndef post_record(fields):\n    payload = {\"fields\": fields}\n    data = json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False).encode('utf-8')\n    req = urllib.request.Request(\n        base_url, data=data,\n        headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {TOKEN}', 'Content-Type': 'application/json; charset=utf-8'},\n        method='POST'\n    )\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req) as r:\n            resp = json.loads(r.read())\n            if resp.get('code') == 0:\n                return f\"OK\"\n            else:\n                return f\"FAIL: {resp.get('code')} {resp.get('msg')}\"\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return f\"HTTP {e.code}: {e.read().decode()[:300]}\"\n\n# Test ALL fields together in one record\nall_fields = {\n    \"文本\": \"2026-05-15 完整测试\",\n    \"商品名称\": \"Kẹp Càng Cua Voan Đính Đá Combo 5 Món - 完整测试\",\n    \"售价本地货币\": 69999,\n    \"月销量\": 5333,\n    \"增长率\": -14.3,\n    \"1688价格CNY\": 8.5,\n    \"预计利润\": 22.5,\n    \"利润率\": 32.1,\n    \"三级类目\": \"发夹\",\n    \"站点\": \"VN\",\n    \"推荐等级\": \"A\",\n    \"采集状态\": \"已采集\",\n    \"IP风险\": \"无\",\n    \"行动建议\": \"正常采购首选30-50件\",\n    \"1688链接\": \"https://detail.1688.com/offer/123456.html\",\n}\n\nprint(\"=== Testing ALL fields together ===\")\nresult = post_record(all_fields)\nprint(f\"Result: {result}\")\n\n# Also try just the problematic fields\nprint(\"\\n=== Testing problematic fields only ===\")\nprob_fields = {\n    \"文本\": \"2026-05-15 仅数值字段测试\",\n    \"商品名称\": \"Test numeric fields only\",\n    \"售价本地货币\": 69999,\n    \"1688价格CNY\": 8.5,\n    \"预计利润\": 22.5,\n    \"利润率\": 32.1,\n}\nresult2 = post_record(prob_fields)\nprint(f\"Result: {result2}\")\n\n# Try string values for numeric fields\nprint(\"\\n=== Testing numeric fields with string values ===\")\nstr_fields = {\n    \"文本\": \"2026-05-15 字符串值\",\n    \"商品名称\": \"Test string values for numbers\",\n    \"售价本地货币\": \"69999\",\n    \"1688价格CNY\": \"8.5\",\n    \"预计利润\": \"22.5\",\n    \"利润率\": \"32.1\",\n}\nresult3 = post_record(str_fields)\nprint(f\"Result: {result3}\")","path":"/tmp/test_feishu4.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":416,"output":1241,"cacheRead":110144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111801,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778853982463,"responseId":"06565b5f961ddaa8e03d0658eb4be493"}}
