{"type":"message","id":"f54eef3a","parentId":"fbb00064","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:07:19.728Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problematic fields fail even in isolation. This is very strange. The error is \"FieldNameNotFound\" which suggests the field names don't exist or aren't recognized.\n\nWait - let me think about this differently. When I tested 增长率 as a standalone field, it worked. But 售价本地货币, 1688价格CNY, 预计利润, 利润率 all fail even alone.\n\nThe difference could be in the field TYPE. Maybe some of these number fields have specific formatting requirements or are computed/lookup fields? But the API returned them as type=2 (Number) with formatter=\"0.0\".\n \nThe field names I'm sending should exactly match what's in the database, but the API says they don't exist - maybe there's a hidden character or space issue in the field names themselves. The fields that fail are the ones with certain naming patterns, so let me try a different approach using just ASCII field names to see if that's the issue.\n","thinkingSignature":"47b1af821ed378dbb133675e9399c8f0aeb6ab3175c9db6a33f516d7748aa93d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0213c7ktca05_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport subprocess, json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\nresult = subprocess.run(['cat', '/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json'], capture_output=True, text=True)\nconfig = json.loads(result.stdout)\ntts = config['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']\nAPP_ID = tts['appId']\nAPP_SECRET = tts['appSecret']\n\nresult = subprocess.run([\n    'curl', '-s', 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal',\n    '-H', 'Content-Type: application/json',\n    '-d', json.dumps({\"app_id\": APP_ID, \"app_secret\": APP_SECRET})\n], capture_output=True, text=True)\nTOKEN = json.loads(result.stdout)['tenant_access_token']\n\n# Get field list to compare exact names\nresult = subprocess.run([\n    'curl', '-s', \n    'ht